{
  "stem": "21812.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so I went on a train and went to London.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Heiers ?] put me up in one of their houses that they had, that they kept for that purpose, and I guess fed me too.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I went to the embassy, United States embassy, and had to apply or do whatever for my visa.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had to go back to Bradford.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it took, I don't know, another month or so before I had to go back again to pick up my visa.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then I left in April via Southampton and again went to London and went to Southampton.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the ship, it was a Dutch ship, the Rotterdam.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it didn't-- by that time, Holland was not in the war yet, hadn't been invaded, so they were a still neutral nation.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was a neutrality zone, which meant that these ships could not-- and England was at war, so the ships could not get into an English harbor.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So they had to stay about three miles outside the harbor.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Well, the ship would lay, and they put us up in a-- in a hotel.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they paid for the hotel, but we had to pay for our own food.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I remember there was a British gentleman who was coming to the United States, old-- older man, and he had family, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But he was going to also leave the country, come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he and I sat at the same table.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And there was this huge dining room.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I had-- I came to United States with $12.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he had to order dinner.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I was faced with the choice of-- of spending my money or saving something for coming here.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
